howtoplay.addons.text.1=Add-Ons are a content type available in the Minecraft Marketplace that lets you add custom blocks, items, mobs, recipes, and other game content to your world.                                                §r§7§o
howtoplay.addons.text.2=Add-Ons allow you to modify your existing worlds and Realms through the Edit World screen and the Create New World screen.                                        §r§7§o
howtoplay.addons.header.1=Stacking Add-Ons                            §r§7§o
howtoplay.addons.text.3=Stacking, or adding multiple Add-Ons, can increase loading times, and could result in unexpected results.                  §r§7§o
howtoplay.addons.text.4=We recommend that you save a copy of your world or Realm before adding or removing Add-Ons.                           §r§7§o
howtoplay.addons.text.5=For more information about how you can make the most out of Add-Ons, you can visit our FAQ page.                        §r§7§o
howtoplay.addons.button.text.1=Add-On FAQs                                  §r§7§o
howtoplay.adventureMode=Adventure Mode                              §r§7§o
howtoplay.adventureMode.text.1=Adventure Mode is a gamemode for world builders. In Adventure Mode, players must use special tools to place or break blocks.                                       §r§7§o
howtoplay.adventureMode.text.2=To get these special tools, you must use §e/give§f with §ecanplace§f or §ecandestroy§f parameters while in creative mode.          §r§7§o§§§§§§
howtoplay.anvil=Anvil                                            §r§7§o
howtoplay.anvil.text.1=Experience Levels can be used to repair, enchant, or rename items with the Anvil.                                               §r§7§o
howtoplay.anvil.header.1=Renaming and Applying Enchantments    §r§7§o
howtoplay.anvil.text.2=All items can be renamed, although only items with durability can be repaired or enchanted with Books on the Anvil.     §r§7§o
howtoplay.anvil.header.2=Repairing                                      §r§7§o
howtoplay.anvil.text.3=An item can be repaired by placing it in one of the input slots on the left, along with either some raw materials of the item, like Iron Ingots for an Iron Sword, or combined with another item of the same type.                                        §r§7§o
howtoplay.anvil.text.4=Combining items is more efficient when done with an Anvil.                             §r§7§o
howtoplay.anvil.text.5=There is a chance that the Anvil will be damaged with each use and after enough usage it will be destroyed.              §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor=Armor                                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.text.1=By wearing Armor, you can protect yourself from incoming damage. Your Armor level is represented by :armor: on the HUD, the higher the level, the less damage you will take.                              §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.header.1=Crafting                                       §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.text.2=Armor can be crafted from Leather, Iron, Gold, or Diamond. Chainmail Armor can be obtained through villager trading and loot from zombies and skeletons.     §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.text.3=Equip Armor by opening your inventory and moving pieces of Armor to the appropriate slot next to your player skin.                                                    §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.text.4=Iron, Chainmail, and Golden Armor can be smelted into Iron or Gold Nuggets in a Furnace.                                      §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.header.2=Shield                                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.text.5.keyboard=The Shield will block incoming damage. The Shield can be equipped in the offhand slot as well as the hotbar. Press and hold :_input_key.sneak: to block with the Shield.                                         §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.text.5.gamepad=The Shield will block incoming damage. The Shield can be equipped in the offhand slot as well as the hotbar. Press :_input_key.sneak: or press :_gamepad_stick_right: to toggle block with the Shield.   §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.text.5a.touch=The Shield blocks all kinds of incoming damage - even a Creeper explosion! It can be equipped in the offhand slot or the hotbar.                                     §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.text.5b.touch=When using the "D-Pad & tap to interact" control scheme, tap :touch_sneak: to toggle blocking with the shield.             §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.text.5c.touch=When using a "Joystick" control scheme, tap :tip_virtual_button_sneak: to toggle blocking with the shield.                   §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.text.6=The Shield can even block a Creeper explosion!                                        §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.header.3=Disguise                                        §r§7§o
howtoplay.armor.text.7=You can also wear a Carved Pumpkin on your head. This won't give you any :armor: but will make it so Endermen won't get mad when you look at them.             §r§7§o
howtoplay.armorStand=Armor Stand                                  §r§7§o
howtoplay.armorStand.text.1=An Armor Stand holds your armor while you aren't using it.                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.armorStand.header.1=Outfitting                                      §r§7§o
howtoplay.armorStand.text.2.notTouch=Press :_input_key.use: on an Armor Stand while holding a piece of armor to place it on the Armor Stand.                   §r§7§o
howtoplay.armorStand.text.2.touch=Tap an Armor Stand while holding a piece of armor to place it on the Armor Stand.                                              §r§7§o
howtoplay.armorStand.text.3.notTouch=Press :_input_key.use: on an Armor Stand with an open hand to remove something from the Armor Stand.                   §r§7§o
howtoplay.armorStand.text.3.touch=Tap an Armor Stand with an open hand to remove something from the Armor Stand.                                              §r§7§o
howtoplay.armorStand.header.2=Posing                                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.armorStand.text.4.notTouch=An Armor Stand can change its pose, sneak and press :_input_key.use: on an Armor Stand to change the pose.          §r§7§o
howtoplay.armorStand.text.4.touch=An Armor Stand can change its pose, sneak and tap an Armor Stand to change the pose.                                      §r§7§o
howtoplay.armorStand.header.3=Dancing                                        §r§7§o
howtoplay.armorStand.text.5=Armor Stands will react to a Redstone signal, try giving it different signal strengths and see what happens.              §r§7§o
howtoplay.banners=Banners                                       §r§7§o
howtoplay.banners.text.1=Banners are a cool way to decorate your house or castle with custom patterns and colors.                                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.banners.text.2=After crafting a Banner, you can put it on a Crafting Table or Loom and add different dyes to create your own unique, cool design!                                §r§7§o
howtoplay.banners.header.1=Applying a Pattern                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.banners.text.3=There are many different patterns that you can create with your dye such as:                                                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.banners.text.4=- Making a triangle will give you a chevron pattern.                                   §r§7§o
howtoplay.banners.text.5=- Making a cross gives you a cross pattern.                                           §r§7§o
howtoplay.banners.text.6=- Use an Oxeye Daisy to craft a flower pattern.                                       §r§7§o
howtoplay.banners.text.7=Experiment with different combinations to get even more patterns!                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.banners.header.2=Multiple Layers                               §r§7§o
howtoplay.banners.text.8=A Banner can also have multiple layers, allowing you to have more than one pattern on your Banner. If you don't like the last pattern you put on a Banner, you can wash the last layer off in a Cauldron.                                           §r§7§o
howtoplay.banners.header.3=Making Copies                                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.banners.text.9=If you want to copy a Banner, put it on the Crafting Table with a blank Banner.                                                  §r§7§o
howtoplay.beacons=Beacons                                       §r§7§o
howtoplay.beacons.text.1=Active Beacons project a bright beam of light into the sky.                         §r§7§o
howtoplay.beacons.text.2=They are crafted with Glass, Obsidian, and Nether Stars (which is obtained by defeating the Wither).                        §r§7§o
howtoplay.beacons.header.1=Construction
howtoplay.beacons.text.3=Beacons need to be on top of a Pyramid of Iron, Gold, Emerald, Diamond, or Netherite blocks with an unobstructed view of the sky.                                    §r§7§o
howtoplay.beacons.text.4=The material that the Beacon is placed on has no effect on the power of the Beacon.                                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.beacons.header.2=Use                                             §r§7§o
howtoplay.beacons.text.5=In the Beacon menu you can select one primary power for your Beacon. The more tiers your pyramid has the more powers you can have.                         §r§7§o
howtoplay.beacons.text.6=To set the powers of your Beacon you must use a Netherite Ingot, Emerald, Diamond, Gold Ingot, or Iron Ingot in the payment slot.                                    §r§7§o
howtoplay.beacons.text.7=Once set, the powers will emanate from the Beacon indefinitely. Powers are granted to all nearby players.                §r§7§o
howtoplay.beacons.text.8=To change the color of the beam, place a stained glass block in its path.        §r§7§o
howtoplay.beds=Beds                                            §r§7§o
howtoplay.beds.text.1=Sleeping in a Bed passes the night and sets your spawn point.                     §r§7§o
howtoplay.beds.text.2.notTouch=Press :_input_key.use: on a Bed to go to sleep. This can only be done at night.                                                   §r§7§o
howtoplay.beds.text.2.touch=Tap a Bed to go to sleep. This can only be done at night.                            §r§7§o
howtoplay.beds.text.3=If you are playing Multiplayer, everyone in the world must be in a Bed at the same time to pass the night.                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.beds.text.4=If your Bed is broken you will return to where you first spawned into the world.                                                §r§7§o
howtoplay.beds.text.5=Be careful when using a Bed in the Nether, it's usually too hot to sleep.         §r§7§o
howtoplay.bedsNew=Beds                                            §r§7§o
howtoplay.bedsNew.title=How to Play: Beds                            §r§7§o
howtoplay.bedsNew.text.1=A soft bed lets you sleep through the night. You'll need wool to craft one, as well as a safe spot to place it.            §r§7§o
howtoplay.bedsNew.text.2=Sleeping in a bed will also set your §espawn point§f, meaning that if you die, you'll reappear right back home!                  §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.bedsNew.text.3=You can only fall asleep when it's cozy, like when it's nighttime or during a thunderstorm.                                      §r§7§o
howtoplay.blocks=Blocks                                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.blocks.text.1=The world of Minecraft is made from millions of blocks. Each one is breakable, collectable, and placeable. There are almost no limits to what you can build!      §r§7§o
howtoplay.blocks.text.2=Most blocks you will have to find in the world, but some can only be crafted such as combining other blocks on a crafting table like a Redstone Block or smelted in a furnace like Glass.                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.blocks.header.1=Falling Blocks                                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.blocks.text.3=Most blocks are not affected by gravity and can float in mid air, but some like Sand and Gravel, will fall if there is no block underneath them.                     §r§7§o
howtoplay.blocks.header.2=Interesting Blocks                           §r§7§o
howtoplay.blocks.text.4=Here are some examples of the more interesting blocks in Minecraft:             §r§7§o
howtoplay.blocks.text.5=§eGlass§f - This is a transparent block that is made by smelting Sand in a Furnace.                                                  §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.blocks.text.6=§eConcrete§f - This is made by dropping a Concrete Powder block into water.       §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.blocks.text.7=§eTerracotta§f - This is found naturally in Badlands biomes or can be crafted and dyed from Clay that is found underwater. Terracotta can be made into Glazed Terracotta by smelting it in a Furnace.                                                  §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.blocks.text.8=§eMagma Block§f - This is found naturally in the Nether, it gives off a little light and will burn whoever steps on it.           §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.blocks.text.9=§eCoarse Dirt§f - This is almost like a normal Dirt block but Grass can't grow on it. It can be found in Windswept Savanna and Old Growth Taiga biomes.                §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.bookAndQuill=Book and Quill                                §r§7§o
howtoplay.bookAndQuill.text.1=The Book and Quill lets you record your adventures. Tell your story by entering text into the pages. You can even change the title and the author! Sign the Book and Quill to finalize your work. The Book and Quill will be editable until it is signed.                                         §r§7§o
howtoplay.brewingStand=Brewing Stand                                §r§7§o
howtoplay.brewingStand.text.1=Brewing potions requires a Brewing Stand. Every potion starts off with a bottle of water, which is made by filling a Glass Bottle with water from a Cauldron or water source.                                §r§7§o
howtoplay.brewingStand.header.1=Know your Brewing Stand                  §r§7§o
howtoplay.brewingStand.text.2=A Brewing Stand has three slots for creating different potions. One ingredient can be used over all three bottles, so always brew three potions at the same time to best use your resources.        §r§7§o
howtoplay.brewingStand.header.2=Ingredients and Potions                    §r§7§o
howtoplay.brewingStand.text.3=Putting Nether Wart in the top position of the Brewing Stand will give you an Awkward Potion. This doesn't have any effect by itself, but creates a base potion that can be used to create more advanced potions.                                   §r§7§o
howtoplay.brewingStand.text.4=There are many potion effects to discover, experiment with different ingredients and combinations to become a true alchemist.                                        §r§7§o
howtoplay.buildingAShelter=Building a Shelter                            §r§7§o
howtoplay.buildingAShelter.title=How to Play: Building a Shelter            §r§7§o
howtoplay.buildingAShelter.text.1=When danger comes lurking, a sturdy §eshelter§f can protect you from the threats outside.                                       §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.buildingAShelter.text.2=Building a shelter is critical to surviving your first night, and it doesn't have to be hard.                                      §r§7§o
howtoplay.buildingAShelter.text.3=You can build one with anything from dirt to stone, or even close up a cave for a makeshift lodging!                       §r§7§o
howtoplay.cauldron=Cauldron                                      §r§7§o
howtoplay.cauldron.text.1=The Cauldron is a container that can hold buckets or bottles of liquid.           §r§7§o
