howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.1=Command Blocks are a powerful tool for map creators. They store and execute commands upon receiving a Redstone signal.                                           §r§7§o
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.2=To get a command block you must use /give.                                             §r§7§o
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.3=When a Command Block has either executed or failed to execute its stored command, it sends a Redstone signal from the side where the arrow is pointing.      §r§7§o
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.4=You can set the name of the Command Block in the Hover Note field.               §r§7§o
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.5=§eBlock Type§f - There are three types of Command Blocks, each with their own color and behavior:                            §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.5.1=§eImpulse§f - Only executes the stored command when the block receives a redstone signal.                                      §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.5.2=§eChain§f - Executes the stored command when the Command Block behind it has or has not executed its command.           §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.5.3=§eRepeat§f - Once activated, this Command Block will continue executing its stored command as long as it exists.              §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.6=§eCondition§f - There are two conditions, each will affect the behavior of the Command Block:                                     §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.6.1=§eUnconditional§f - Executes the stored command even if the Command Block behind it failed to execute its command.         §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.6.2=§eConditional§f - Only executes the stored command if the Command Block behind it succeeded in executing its command.    §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.7=§eRedstone§f - There are two redstone settings, each will affect the behavior of the Command Block:                           §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.7.1=§eNeeds Redstone§f - Requires a redstone signal to activate.                           §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.7.2=§eAlways Active§f - Does not require a redstone signal to activate.                    §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.commandBlocks.text.8=A Command Block will also show you its previous output. This will help you figure out if a Command Block failed to execute its command and why.                     §r§7§o
howtoplay.commands=Commands                                      §r§7§o
howtoplay.commands.text.1=Commands can be executed from Chat. Type / before you type the command.    §r§7§o
howtoplay.commands.text.2=There are multitudes of commands that will allow you to do amazing things. There are many sources out there that will provide you with all of the info that you'll ever need.                                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.conduits=Conduits
howtoplay.conduits.text.1=An active Conduit gives you powers when you are underwater and when it rains.                                                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.conduits.text.2=A Conduit is crafted with Nautilus Shells and a Heart of the Sea. The Conduit draws power from Prismarine and Sea Lanterns.                                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.conduits.header.1=Construction
howtoplay.conduits.text.3=Once activated, a Conduit will grant Conduit Power to anything nearby.            §r§7§o
howtoplay.conduits.text.4=The more power it draws in, the further its abilities reach.                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.craftingATool=Crafting a Tool                               §r§7§o
howtoplay.craftingATool.title=How to Play: Crafting a Tool               §r§7§o
howtoplay.craftingATool.text.1=§eTools§f help you get things done faster. Some, like the §epickaxe§f:wood_pickaxe: , let you mine stone and various ores. Others, like the §esword§f:wood_sword: , help you keep enemies at bay.                      §r§7§o§§§§§§
howtoplay.craftingATool.text.2.keyboard=To craft a tool, open up your §ecrafting table§f:crafting_table: by walking up to it and right-clicking it. You can craft a basic version of most tools using two sticks and a few planks - your §erecipe book§f will tell you how!                             §r§7§o§§§§
howtoplay.craftingATool.text.2.gamepad=To craft a tool, open up your §ecrafting table§f:crafting_table: by walking up to it and pressing :_input_key.use:. You can craft a basic version of most tools using two sticks and a few planks - your §erecipe book§f will tell you how!                 §r§7§o§§§§
howtoplay.craftingATool.text.2.touch=To craft a tool, open up your §ecrafting table§f:crafting_table: by walking up to it and tapping it. You can craft a basic version of most tools using two sticks and a few planks - your §erecipe book§f will tell you how!                                     §r§7§o§§§§
howtoplay.worldBuilder=World Builder                                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.worldBuilder.title=How to Play: World Builder                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.worldBuilder.text.1=To place or use certain Minecraft Education blocks or items, a player must possess a special ability called 'World Builder'.                                             §r§7§o
howtoplay.worldBuilder.text.2=With cheats activated, the host can enable or disable the World Builder ability for any players in the world.              §r§7§o
howtoplay.worldBuilder.text.3=To grant World Builder ability to all players in the world, run the following command:                                            §r§7§o
howtoplay.worldBuilder.text.4=/ability @a worldbuilder true
howtoplay.worldBuilder.text.5=To quickly toggle your own World Builder ability, run either of the following commands:                                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.worldBuilder.text.6=/worldbuilder
howtoplay.worldBuilder.text.7=/wb
howtoplay.worldBuilder.text.8=To query your World Builder ability, run the following command:                     §r§7§o
howtoplay.worldBuilder.text.9=/ability @p worldbuilder
