howtoplay.creativeMode.text.1=Creative Mode is there so you can build the land of your dreams mob free!     §r§7§o
howtoplay.creativeMode.header.1=Unlimited Building                             §r§7§o
howtoplay.creativeMode.text.2=The creative mode interface allows any item in the game to be moved into the player's inventory without the need for mining or crafting the item. The items in the player's inventory will not be removed when they are placed or used in the world, and this allows the player to focus on building rather than resource gathering.                                        §r§7§o
howtoplay.creativeMode.text.3=If you create, load, or save a world in Creative Mode, that world will have achievements and leaderboard updates disabled, even if it is then loaded in Survival Mode.                                         §r§7§o
howtoplay.creativeMode.header.2=Flying                                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.creativeMode.text.4.keyboard=To fly when in Creative Mode, press :_input_key.jump: twice quickly. To exit flying, repeat the action. To fly faster, push :_input_key.forward: twice in rapid succession or press :_input_key.sprint: while flying. When in flying mode, you can hold down :_input_key.jump: to move up and :_input_key.sneak: to move down.       §r§7§o
howtoplay.creativeMode.text.4.gamepad=To fly when in Creative Mode, press :_input_key.jump: twice quickly. To exit flying, repeat the action. To fly faster, push :_gamepad_stick_left: forward twice in rapid succession while flying. When in flying mode, you can hold down :_input_key.jump: to move up and :_input_key.sneak: to move down.                              §r§7§o
howtoplay.creativeMode.text.4a.touch.joystick_tap_and_crosshair=To fly tap :tip_virtual_button_jump: twice quickly, and to stop flying tap :tip_virtual_button_fly_down: twice quickly.      §r§7§o
howtoplay.creativeMode.text.4b.touch.joystick_tap_and_crosshair=Tap :tip_virtual_button_sprint: to fly faster. To fly up tap and hold :tip_virtual_button_fly_up:, and to fly down tap and hold :tip_virtual_button_fly_down:.      §r§7§o
howtoplay.creativeMode.text.4a.touch.classic_dpad=To fly tap :touch_jump: twice quickly, and to stop flying tap :touch_stop_flying: twice quickly.                                  §r§7§o
howtoplay.creativeMode.text.4b.touch.classic_dpad=Tap :touch_forward: twice quickly to fly faster. To fly up tap and hold :touch_fly_up:, and to fly down tap and hold :touch_fly_down:.                                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.deathAndRespawn=Death and Respawn                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.deathAndRespawn.title=How to Play: Death and Respawn          §r§7§o
howtoplay.deathAndRespawn.text.1=Enemies appear every night, and even the best of us can be caught off guard. If your §ehealth bar§f:heart: runs out, you'll die - and then respawn right where you started!                                  §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.deathAndRespawn.text.2=You have unlimited lives, but you drop all items in your inventory when you die. If you're quick enough, you can pick your items back up right where you dropped them.                                        §r§7§o
howtoplay.difficulty=Difficulty                                      §r§7§o
howtoplay.difficulty.text.1=Minecraft has varying levels of difficulty so you can tailor the game to your level.                                             §r§7§o
howtoplay.difficulty.header.1=Peaceful                                       §r§7§o
howtoplay.difficulty.text.2=No hostile mobs will spawn except for shulkers and the Ender Dragon, but they won't do any damage to you.              §r§7§o
howtoplay.difficulty.header.2=Easy                                            §r§7§o
howtoplay.difficulty.text.3=Hostile mobs spawn but deal less damage. Hunger bar depletes and drains health down to 5 hearts.                        §r§7§o
howtoplay.difficulty.header.3=Normal                                         §r§7§o
howtoplay.difficulty.text.4=Hostile mobs will do normal damage, and if your hunger level drops to zero your health will begin to drop, but you won't die.                                            §r§7§o
howtoplay.difficulty.header.4=Hard                                            §r§7§o
howtoplay.difficulty.text.5=Hostile mobs will do more damage, zombies will break through doors, and if your hunger level drops to zero, your health will drop and you could die.            §r§7§o
howtoplay.dispensers=Dispensers                                    §r§7§o
howtoplay.dispensers.text.1=Dispensers are used to shoot out items. You will need to power each Dispenser with a redstone signal (for example, with a lever) to trigger it.                    §r§7§o
howtoplay.dispensers.text.2.notTouch=To fill a Dispenser with items, press :_input_key.use: on the Dispenser, then move the items that you want to dispense from your inventory to the Dispenser.   §r§7§o
howtoplay.dispensers.text.2.touch=To fill a Dispenser, tap the Dispenser, then move the items that you want to dispense from your inventory into the Dispenser.                                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.dispensers.header.1=Usage                                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.dispensers.text.3=Whenever you power a Dispenser, an item will shoot out.                              §r§7§o
howtoplay.dispensers.text.4=Dispensers can also be used to place items as well, such as Pumpkins on Iron Golems and equipment on Armor Stands.                                                   §r§7§o
howtoplay.droppers=Droppers
howtoplay.droppers.text.1.notTouch=When powered by Redstone, Droppers will drop a single random item contained within. Press :_input_key.use: on the Dropper to open it and then you can load it with items from your inventory.          §r§7§o
howtoplay.droppers.text.1.touch=When powered by Redstone, Droppers will drop a single random item contained within. Tap the Dropper to open it and then you can load it with items from your inventory.                                     §r§7§o
howtoplay.droppers.header.1=Usage                                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.droppers.text.2=If a Dropper is facing a Chest or another type of container, the item will be placed into that instead. Long chains of Droppers can be constructed to transport items over a distance.                  §r§7§o
howtoplay.dyes=Dyes                                            §r§7§o
howtoplay.dyes.text.1=Dye is used to change the color of many things in Minecraft.                       §r§7§o
howtoplay.dyes.text.2=Some Dye materials are harder to find than others. Most Dyes can be crafted from flowers, like §eRed Dye§f from a Poppy, but some Dyes are found or created in more obscure ways such as:           §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.dyes.text.3=§eBlue Dye§f - Mining Lapis Lazuli deep underground                                      §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.dyes.text.4=§eBlack Dye§f - Collecting Ink Sacs from Squids                                             §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.dyes.text.5=§eBrown Dye§f - Harvesting Cocoa Beans in the Jungle                                   §r§7§o§§
