howtoplay.theCraftingTable.title=How to Play: The Crafting Table          §r§7§o
howtoplay.theCraftingTable.text.1=Ready to take your crafting to the next level? Place four planks in a square in your crafting grid, and you'll get a §ecrafting table§f :crafting_table: - a whole new way to craft.                             §r§7§o§§
howtoplay.theCraftingTable.text.2.keyboard=Place your crafting table in the world, then right-click it to open it. The larger crafting grid will let you make bigger and better things, including tools, beds, and doors.                                      §r§7§o
howtoplay.theCraftingTable.text.2.gamepad=Place your crafting table in the world, then walk up to it and press :_input_key.use: to open it. The larger crafting grid will let you make bigger and better things, including tools, beds, and doors.    §r§7§o
howtoplay.theCraftingTable.text.2.touch=Place your crafting table in the world, then tap it to open it. The larger crafting grid will let you make bigger and better things, including tools, beds, and doors.                                               §r§7§o
howtoplay.theEnd=The End                                        §r§7§o
howtoplay.theEnd.text.1=The End is another dimension which can be accessed through an active End Portal. The End Portal can be found in a Stronghold, which is deep underground in the Overworld.                             §r§7§o
howtoplay.theEnd.text.2=Every End Portal Frame block is missing something mysterious to bring out the power within.                                  §r§7§o
howtoplay.theEnd.header.1=The Other Side                               §r§7§o
howtoplay.theEnd.text.3=Once the portal is active, jump into it to go to The End.                              §r§7§o
howtoplay.theEnd.text.4=The End is home to the dreaded Ender Dragon. She is a fierce and powerful enemy and seems to draw power from strange crystals. Her breath and fireball attacks leave lingering acid across the battlefield. Bring some friends to ensure your victory!                              §r§7§o
howtoplay.theEnd.text.5=If once wasn't enough, add four End Crystals to the exit portal corners to reawaken the Ender Dragon.                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.textures=Textures
howtoplay.textures.text.1=Texture packs visually transform the game's appearance, applying a fresh coat of paint to your Minecraft world.      §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools=Tools                                           §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.1=There are many tools in Minecraft that will allow you mine blocks faster than your fist. Tools can be crafted from Wood, Stone, Iron, Gold, Diamond, or Netherite.                                                §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.2=Using the right tool for the job will not only mine that block faster, but will also lose less durability. More complex tools must be created in order to mine rarer resources.                                §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.header.1=Tools that Break Stuff                     §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.3=The Pickaxe is good at breaking hard blocks like Cobblestone, Iron, or Furnaces.                                               §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.4=The Axe is good at breaking wooden blocks like Logs, Planks, or Crafting Tables.                                                §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.5.notTouch=The Shovel is good at breaking loose blocks like Dirt, Sand, and Gravel. Shovels can also create a path by pressing :_input_key.use: on grass blocks.           §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.5.touch=The Shovel is good at breaking loose blocks like Dirt, Sand, and Gravel. Shovels can also create a path by tapping on grass blocks.                                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.6.notTouch=The Hoe is required for tilling Dirt to plant crops. Press :_input_key.use: on Dirt or Grass blocks to turn them into Farmland.                                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.6.touch=The Hoe is required for tilling Dirt to plant crops. Tap Dirt or Grass blocks to turn them into Farmland.                   §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.7=All of these tools can accept enchantments, either from the Enchanting Table or Anvil.                                        §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.header.2=Other Tools                                   §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.8=There are even more tools to aid you on your adventure:                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.9=A Bucket will allow you to collect things like Water, Milk, Lava, and even Fish.     §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.10=Flint & Steel allows you to light fires... be careful in densely wooded areas!     §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.11=A Fishing Rod lets you catch fish and other loot from water blocks. It can also be used to pull other players and mobs. Fishing Rods can also be enchanted!                                                   §r§7§o
howtoplay.tools.text.12=Shears are very handy for collecting items like Wool, Leaves, and Cobwebs.     §r§7§o
howtoplay.trading=Villager Trading                              §r§7§o
howtoplay.trading.text.1=Trading can be done in villages. Each villager has a profession; they can be Farmers, Butchers, Blacksmiths, Cartographers, Librarians, or Priests. Some professions will trade for items that other professions cannot. Explore and trade with many villagers to find all the trades.                                                §r§7§o
howtoplay.trading.header.1=Goods for Emeralds                         §r§7§o
howtoplay.trading.text.2=You can find out what a villager is offering as trade by interacting with them. A villager may adjust the price of a trade whenever a player trades with it. A villager may run out of stock, temporarily disabling the trade if it is used too frequently. Trades usually involve buying or selling items for emeralds.           §r§7§o
howtoplay.trading.text.3=As you trade with villagers, they will get better at their profession and start to offer better and more valuable trades.                                               §r§7§o
howtoplay.trading.text.4=Take care of your villagers, they need to rest, work, and eat to thrive.         §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation=Transportation                               §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.1=There are many ways to get around other than walking or riding a mount or flying.                                             §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.header.1=Minecarts                                      §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.2=Minecarts are ridable carts that roll on Rails. You can make the Rails go wherever you want by placing them next to each other. Place a Minecart on the Rails and you are ready to ride.               §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.2.touch=Minecarts are ridable carts that roll on Rails, which you can build to go anywhere. Just place multiple Rails next to each other, place a Minecart on it, and you're ready to ride.                           §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.3.keyboard=Press :_input_key.use: while looking at a Minecart to hop in and ride. Press :_input_key.forward: to roll forward. Press :_input_key.jump: or :_input_key.sneak: to get out.                                      §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.3.gamepad=Press :_input_key.use: while looking at a Minecart to hop in and ride. Push :_gamepad_stick_left: forward to roll forward. Press :_input_key.jump: or :_input_key.sneak: to get out.                           §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.3a.touch=Look at a Minecart and tap "Ride" to hop in.                                             §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.3b.touch=When using the D-Pad control scheme, tap and hold :touch_forward: to start moving forward and build momentum, and tap :touch_jump: to get out.                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.3c.touch=When using a Joystick control scheme, drag :tip_virtual_joystick: up to start moving forward and build momentum, and tap :tip_virtual_button_dismount: to get out.                                               §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.header.2=Boats                                           §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.4=Boats let you travel across water. Place one on a water block and you are ready to go.                                     §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.4.touch=Boats let you travel across water. Just place one on a water block and you're ready to go.                                 §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.5.keyboard=Press :_input_key.use: while looking at a Boat to board it. Press :_input_key.left: or :_input_key.right: to turn left or right. Press :_input_key.forward: to move forward. Press :_input_key.jump: or :_input_key.sneak: to get out.                   §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.5.gamepad=Press :_input_key.use: while looking at a Boat to board it. Push :_gamepad_stick_left: left or right to turn. Push :_gamepad_stick_left: forward to move forward. Press :_input_key.jump: or :_input_key.sneak: to get out.                            §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.5a.touch=Look at a Boat and tap "Board" to board it.                                             §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.5b.touch=When using the D-Pad control scheme, tap :touch_left: or :touch_right: to turn left or right, or tap and hold both to move forward. Tap "Leave Boat" to get out.                                                §r§7§o
howtoplay.transportation.text.5c.touch=When using a Joystick control scheme, drag :tip_virtual_joystick: up to move forward and tap :tip_virtual_button_dismount: to get out.                                §r§7§o
howtoplay.weapons=Weapons                                       §r§7§o
howtoplay.weapons.header.1=Sword                                          §r§7§o
howtoplay.weapons.text.1=The Sword is the primary melee weapon in Minecraft. It can be made from Wood, Stone, Iron, Gold, Diamond, or Netherite. Jump attacks do critical damage!         §r§7§o
howtoplay.weapons.text.2.notTouch=Press :_input_key.attack: with a Sword in your hand to attack.                      §r§7§o
howtoplay.weapons.text.2.touch=Tap mobs to attack them.                   §r§7§o
howtoplay.weapons.header.2=Bow                                             §r§7§o
howtoplay.weapons.text.3.notTouch=The Bow is the primary ranged weapon in Minecraft. Press and hold :_input_key.use: to draw the bow back. Release :_input_key.use: to fire an arrow. The bow requires arrows to fire.                    §r§7§o
