lategameTips.11=Traveling one block in the Nether is equal to traveling eight blocks in the Overworld.                                           §r§7§o
lategameTips.12=Use phantom membranes to repair your elytra.                                         §r§7§o
lategameTips.13=Elytra can be used to glide, find them in End city ships!                              §r§7§o
lategameTips.14=Test out some new features by turning on Experimental Gameplay in the settings menu!                                         §r§7§o
lategameTips.15=Monsters that are killed by skeletons arrows have a chance of dropping music discs.                                          §r§7§o
lategameTips.16=Texture packs change the way that blocks, items, and even the menus look in game. Try them out!                            §r§7§o
lategameTips.17=Using firework rockets boosts elytra speed in mid air. Just... make sure they don't explode, otherwise it'll hurt BADLY!                                                    §r§7§o
lategameTips.18=Do people actually read these?          §r§7§o
lategameTips.19=Riptide enchantment will propel you through the air in the rain.                     §r§7§o
lategameTips.20=The Beacon is a powerful item that can only be crafted with a Nether star from the Wither!                                   §r§7§o
lategameTips.21=Nether stars can't be destroyed by explosions.                                       §r§7§o
lategameTips.22=You can barter with piglins.               §r§7§o
lategameTips.23=Respawning in the Nether requires a charged respawn anchor.                    §r§7§o
lategameTips.24=You can charge a respawn anchor with glowstone.                                    §r§7§o
lategameTips.25=You can breed hoglins with crimson fungus, but be careful.                         §r§7§o
lategameTips.26=Gold is most common in the Nether and in the badlands biome.                        §r§7§o
lategameTips.27=Diorite, you either love it or hate it.     §r§7§o
tips.realms.1=Take a screenshot using the Game menu.
tips.realms.2=A Realm is always online, so you and your friends can play here whenever you want.
tips.realms.3=Keep up to date with what's going on in your Realm by checking the Story Feed in Realms Stories.
tips.realms.4=Share your great moments with the other players on this Realm by adding a story to the Story Feed.
tips.realms.5=Check the Timeline in Realms Stories to find out when others are playing.
tips.realms.6=Access Realms Stories from the game menu while playing on the Realm.
tips.realms.7=Get to know your Realm's community on the Members tab in Realms Stories.
tips.realms.8=Use Realms Stories to get social, keep up with your friends' progress, and organize playtime.
tips.creative.1=Bored of gravity? Jump twice to fly!
tips.creative.2=Summon mobs in an instant with spawn eggs.
tips.creative.3=Collect goat horns and fill the world with music.
tips.creative.4=Combine flint and steel with a TNT block for explosive results.
tips.creative.5=Try blinking around the map with an ender pearl. Don't get dizzy!
tips.creative.6=Use rails and a minecart to build the perfect transport system. Or rollercoaster!
tips.creative.7=Seeking a little more danger? Survival mode has plenty.
tips.creative.8=Crossbows need ammo. Add some arrows to your inventory before going hunting.
tips.creative.9=You can't die, but villagers can. Use that information... wisely.
tips.creative.10=Villagers are great at building villages. Think you can do better?
tips.creative.11=Wolves will attack skeletons to chew on their tasty bones.
tips.creative.12=Tame wild horses by sitting on them until they're calm, then saddle up and ride off. (Note: Horses do not work like that outside of Minecraft.)
tips.creative.13=Eat as much as you want, you'll never get full! And you'll never starve.
tips.creative.14=Move through solid objects using spectator mode.
tips.creative.15=Who needs tools? Punch your way to success and remove blocks instantly in creative mode.
tips.creative.16=Like what you see? Use the pick block button to start building with whatever you're looking at. Yes, even mobs!
tips.creative.17=Get there now with the /tp command.
tips.creative.18=Mobs won't notice you in creative mode, but they'll still notice each other...
tips.creative.19=A warden a day keeps the... well, everything away.
tips.creative.20=Why not build an underwater base? It's not like you can drown.
tips.creative.21=Whatever you can dream, you can build. There's no limit to your resources (in creative mode...).
tips.creative.22=Phantoms can't hurt you, but you can still shoo them off by using a bed. Just...not literally. You sleep in it.
tips.creative.23=Have you tried swimming in lava? It's like sinking into a warm bath. Just don't try it in survival mode...
